				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The NES connector is metric, it's 2.5mm.  The pins will get shorted in a .1" (2.54mm) connector.  A game genie sounds like the way to go.  Another source of connectors would be a cheap clone that takes NES carts.
<br />
<br />The Famicom connector, however is .1" pitch (2.54mm).
<br />
<br />As for wireless, there was a company called Messiah a while back, that had released some wireless controllers.  The receiver shouldn't need power (the NES controller port supplies +5V).</div>

